aa(lp93
VThe other half of the audience doesn't like head-tail-tail \u2014
p94
aVthey think, for deep cultural reasons, that's boring \u2014
p95
aVand they're much more interested in a different pattern \u2014 head-tail-head.
p96
aVSo, on this side, you get out your coins, and you toss and toss and toss.
p97
aVAnd you count the number of times until the pattern head-tail-head appears
p98
aVand you average them. OK?
p99
aVSo on this side, you've got a number \u2014
p100
